main event: A report from Project Blue Book detailing a sighting of a UFO, likely a meteor, observed on January 12, 1959.
interesting points: The sighting reportedly lasted for 6 seconds., The object was described as cigar-shaped and approximately 15 feet long., Witnesses included a reliable farmer who does not drink., The weather was generally good at the time of the sighting., Photographic evidence is present, though the quality is insufficient for a detailed description.
witness description: a 69-year-old farmer from Rice, Washington, very reliable and does not drink
